DOC.brief_summary: Elevation of serum progesterone on the day of ovulation triggering in IVF/ICSI cycles is suggested to be associated with compromized outcomes. Others found that this rise didnot affect the IVF/ICSI outcomes. It is still controversal if premature luteinization would affect the IVF/ICSI outcomes.
DOC.criteria: Planned fresh Embryo transfer Cancelation of the embryo transfer for any reason
